messages.speech:
Century College has a standard printer naming convention for all campus printers. Printers are named and labeled first by room number then by printer model number. There are 3 printers in each computer center labeled for easy verification.

East:

    E1710-7535 - This is the main color printer in the East Campus Computer Center.
    E1710-5775 - This is the main black & white printer in the East Campus Computer Center.
    E1710-602 - This is the backup black & white printer in the East Campus Computer Center. There will be signs posted within the computer center and an announcement made when this printer is to be used.

West:

    W3165-7535 - This is the main color printer in the West Campus Computer Center.
    W3165-5775 - This is the main black & white printer in the West Campus Computer Center.
    W3165-602 - This is the backup black & white printer in the West Campus Computer Center. There will be signs posted within the computer center and an announcement made when this printer is to be used.
